name: Ice Skating
description: Open October to March. Hosts competitions for local teams. Free entry, skate rental is 3chf for kids  and 5 for adults. Has a bistrot where you can get drinks and meals are served lunch time Wed - Sun and every evening until 11pm. Get down at the ice disco on Friday nights :)

name: Skatepark of Plainpalais
description: When the menace known as The Joker emerges from his mysterious past, he wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham. The Dark Knight must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.
category: Adventure Sports, Parks and Skate Parks

name: Olympic Museum
description: The Olympic Museum (French: Musée olympique) in Lausanne, Switzerland houses permanent and temporary exhibits relating to sport and the Olympic movement. With more than 10,000 artifacts, the museum is the largest archive of Olympic Games in the world and one of Lausanne's prime tourist site draws attracting more than 250,000 visitors each year

name: Arboretum Aubonne
description: The Arboretum du Vallon de l'Aubonne is spread over nearly 200 ha of forests and meadows. This area is fully available to the public. Many walking paths welcome you to dive into the majestic universe of trees. The arboretum is home to more than 3000 species and varieties of trees and shrubs mainly coming from temperate regions of the globe.

name: FC St Prex
description:
FC Amical St-Prex football club is open to all young people, boys and girls, from the age of 6.

Training takes place on Wednesdays from 6:00 p.m. to 7:30 p.m. at the Vieux-Moulin field. The goal of the club is to allow children to meet together outside of school, to learn the control of the ball and especially to have fun.
address: Vieux Moulin, Avenue de Taillecou 2, 1162 Saint-Prex

name: Les Tetards Scuba School
description: All children from 8 years are welcome, whether they dive regularly or occasionally, whether their parents are divers or not. During each dive, children are accompanied by experienced instructors specially trained in children's diving.

name: TOTEM Indoor Climbing Wall
description: TOTEM offers a unique and friendly urban space which, in a relaxed atmosphere, allows everyone to satisfy their passion for fun, sport and climbing. If you are a beginner, come learn to climb with our experienced instructors. Climbing is the new urban sport that will allow you to get in shape while having fun with your friends or family.

name: Coquino Circus School
description: The Coquino circus school is above all a favorite for children, the circus, the joy of life and laughter… Frédéric Klink, director and his 20 employees make every effort to take young budding artists in a very playful universe.

name: Capoeira - La Tête en l'Air
description: Capoeira is an Afro-Brazilian Martial Art which mixes combat, dance, song and acrobatics on traditional Brazilian rhythms. This discipline develops strength, flexibility, self-defense, self-confidence and musical ability. It will allow children to wake up through games of agility, flexibility and rhythm.
address: Ateliers de la Côte, route de Pallatex 5, 1163 Etoy
